    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith the recent release of the v0.12 series snapd helpfully updated my installation, which promptly broke due to breaking changes in Treesitter. This behavior was replicated across several machines, all of which needed manual intervention to fix.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nBreaking changes are a fact of life, but it would be nice if channels could be added for each release series for those that don't want to update to `latest/stable` immediately. Something along the lines of `latest/v0.12` or `latest/v0.11` would be fantastic. At the very least, if we can have a channel for the previous stable to give time for plugins and configuration to be updated would be very helpful.\n\nFor what it's worth, this is a common issue with snaps. Snap has washed their hands of this and has punted to each publisher to manage versions. There does not seem to be a way to revert to an older version unless it is provided by a channel. As a result, I've had to stop using the nvim snap in favor of AppImages until this can be resolved.",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-28T23:11:53Z",
